# Cursor AI Rules for SimpleAI WebAdmin

Read and strictly follow guidelines in AGENTS.md before making any code changes.

## Critical Rules

1. Generic examples ONLY - use neutral terms: records, items, users, categories, data
2. Dark mode MANDATORY - every component needs dark: classes
3. Design system consistency:
   - Colors: zinc palette + blue-purple gradients
   - Spacing: gap-5/6/7, p-6/7/8, space-y-10
   - Shadows: shadow-md/lg/xl (increase on hover)
   - Border-radius: rounded-xl/2xl/3xl
4. Responsive: test at sm:/lg:/xl: breakpoints
5. Accessibility: semantic HTML, aria-labels, keyboard nav

## File Patterns

Dashboard widgets → app/(main)/dashboard/page.tsx
Sidebar links → components/Sidebar.tsx  
API routes → app/api/
Components → components/
Utils → lib/

## Security

SQL: Only SELECT/SHOW/DESCRIBE/EXPLAIN (validated in lib/safety.ts)
Secrets: Use .env.local (never commit)

## Before Submitting

✓ Generic, neutral content only
✓ Dark mode complete
✓ Responsive design checked
✓ No console errors
✓ Matches design system

See AGENTS.md for full guidelines.
